The article is a statement from the President on the passing of Walter Cronkite. The President describes Cronkite as the most trusted voice in America and someone who set the standard for others in the industry. Cronkite was known for calmly informing viewers about wars, riots, marches, and milestones, never losing his integrity. He was described as more than just an anchor, but as someone who guided the public through important issues. The President refers to Cronkite as family, someone who was believed in and never let anyone down. The President concludes by stating that Cronkite's passing is a loss for the country and that he will be truly missed.